subtitle: Stay away from smoky places
title: Why am I breathless?
content:
Created by babyCenter


Even if you've never felt breathless before, like lots of women, you may sometimes feel breathless now. This is normal. Your body is adapting, and growing a baby!

You can help your breathing by keeping away from dirty air and smoky places.

Do you smoke? Stop, or cut down now. It is bad for your health and for your baby’s health. Remember, you can save the money you spend on smoking to buy things you will need during pregnancy and for the baby.

Ask your family to smoke outside.

If you are breathless all the time, you may be anemic. This means your body lacks iron. Taking iron tablets will help. You can also make sure you eat a variety of different foods like leafy vegetables, eggs, fruit, beans, lentils and poultry. They all help your body to get iron.
